WorkItem.Description:
I have a bunch of .less files that are imported into my main styles.chirp.less to better organize all the css I have.  My styles.chirp.less file looks kind of like

@import "reset";
@import "960gs";
@import "common";
@import "sidebar";

with a few more imports.  Needless to say it doesn't change that often while I'm debugging, but all the .less files it's including do change often.  Problem is that chirpy doesn't rebuild the styles.css again unless I touch styles.chirp.css.  Please make chirpy watch for changes in dependencies.  Also, I thought I could work around it with a quick CRTL+SHIFT+B build of the project, but chirpy doesn't even rebuild css files when I build the project.
